description:
At Jabil we strive to make ANYTHING POSSIBLE and EVERYTHING BETTER. With over 260,000 diverse, talented and dedicated employees across 100 locations in 30 countries, our vision is to be the most technologically advanced and trusted manufacturing solutions provider. We combine an unmatched breadth and depth of end-market experience, technical and design capabilities, manufacturing know-how, supply... chain insights and global product management expertise to enable success for the world's leading brands. We are driven by a common purpose to make a positive impact for each other, our communities, and the environment.

Radius, part of Jabil Innovation & Development is searching for a UI/UX Lead who is passionate about leading project teams, adept at creating innovative digital solutions and experiences. This position will report to the Director of Innovation.
• **Consulting Experience Highly Desired in this Role***

WHY JOIN US:

We are the innovation consulting arm of Jabil, the most technologically advanced manufacturing solutions provider in the world. Together we are the only end-to-end innovation consulting business committed to solving our clients' toughest challenges.

With the multi-disciplinary strengths of strategists, researchers, human factors specialists, designers, and conceptual engineers, we help clients identify as well as capitalize on the next game-changing opportunity - through experiences and products designed to win. We can be best described as change agents, entrepreneurial professionals backed by a large, established Fortune 100 organization.

WHAT YOU ARE:

We are looking for a strong lead consultant to help build out our UI/UX offering. We are looking for someone who can inspire fellow researchers and designers and lead with both empathy and conviction for the people we design for. You have a passion for solving complex problems and driving digital/customer solutions. As UI/UX Lead, you will play a crucial role throughout the entire project process - using research to inspire our design teams, inform better prototypes, and elevate the perspective of our clients.

WHAT YOU WILL DO:
• Responsible for shaping digital solutions and properly scoping engagements, establishing project charters and project team organization;
• Serve as an expert digital consultant leading Digital Business Transformation initiatives and producing relevant deliverables;
• Translate user experience strategies into beautifully designed, tangible on-screen experiences;
• Serve as the client engagement lead, responsible for digital and customer engagement strategies and program roadmaps;
• Stay abreast of current and emerging trends, unique opportunities and challenges of our clients industries;
• Establish and cultivate strong relationships with clients at senior levels as well as external and internal partners to maximize growth;
• Develop and maintain internal and external relationships to deliver results as we scale our team.
• Understand the intersection between technology, customers, and business
• Leading the transition from the sales process to the delivery phase;
• Understand the full end-end product cycle, from product vision/strategy, user experience design through development and release;
• Align with Senior Leadership to co-develop / lead account plans and strategies for delivery, growth, and client satisfaction;
• Support sales / pre-sales activities by assessing digital, innovation & design opportunities, responding to RFP's, creating proposals and presentations, establishing relationships with clients and prospective clients, and helping to close new deals;
• Directly manage designers, researchers, strategists and CX consultants, understanding their professional ambitions, guiding their careers, and growing their skills;
• build connections with other team members, assign mentors and share work between studios.

MINIMUM EDUCATIONAL & EXPERIENCE REQUIREMENTS:
• 8+ years of qualitative research experience, with solid experience in Healthcare, ideally in a consulting environment;
• Passion for leading teams and teaching others about digital solutions;
• Awareness of technical platforms, business models, subject matter, and trends - with a focus on digital;
• Skilled in areas of consumer/user research and analysis, personas and customer journeys, ideation and brainstorming techniques, sketching, prototyping, and concept validation;
• Skilled in developing requirements, developing architecture, navigation and wireframes and producing low and high fidelity prototypes;
• Strong design skills specifically in embedded UI's with experience in standalone (apps/web) UI a bonus;
• Strong problem solver and creative thinker;
• Strong digital knowledge or experience with particular emphasis on strategy, consulting, team management and product development;
• Track record of leading and managing teams;
• Strong presentation skills with a creative and compelling storytelling style;
• Business and consulting savvy, with an ability to think strategically;
• Innate curiosity, and a passion for telling compelling human stories;

BE AWARE OF FRAUD: When applying for a job at Jabil you will be contacted via correspondence through our official job portal with a jabil.com e-mail address; direct phone call from a member of the Jabil team; or direct e-mail with a jabil.com e-mail address. Jabil does not request payments for interviews or at any other point during the hiring process. Jabil will not ask for your personal identifying information such as a social security number, birth certificate, financial institution, driver's license number or passport information over the phone or via e-mail. If you believe you are a victim of identity theft, contact the Federal Bureau of Investigations internet crime hotline (www.ic3.gov), the Federal Trade Commission identity theft hotline (www.identitytheft.gov) and/or your local police department. Any scam job listings should be reported to whatever website it was posted in.

This job cannot be performed remotely in the state of Colorado.

Jabil, including its subsidiaries, is an equal opportunity employer and considers qualified applicants for employment without regard to race, color, religion, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identify, age, disability, genetic information, veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by law

